                            <comment id="14466737" author="roshandawrani" created="Sat, 4 Apr 2009 09:45:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It does not really seem to be related to import static feature because even compilation of the following fails. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Pretty basic usage. Seems to be a serious bug! &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It can&apos;t see groovy classes of the same package!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A.groovy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; foo

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;A {}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;B.groovy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; foo

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;B {
  def baz() {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; A()
  }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466791" author="blackdrag" created="Mon, 6 Apr 2009 06:14:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;for B to find A.groovy during compilation A.groovy has to be in a directory foo and the directory containing foo has to be in the classpath.  Or both files have to be given to the compiler.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14466845" author="blackdrag" created="Mon, 6 Apr 2009 06:17:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;as for the static import.. I am a bit puzzled as of why A.bar works, but A.* does not.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466758" author="roshandawrani" created="Mon, 6 Apr 2009 06:27:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see. I just put the files in the same directory but other things you said were not followed. I will put them there and re-try the original issue reported here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466901" author="roshandawrani" created="Fri, 1 May 2009 16:31:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
